HEADWORD: Stearolic
<hw>Ste`a*rol"ic</hw> <pr>(-r⟦ocr⟧l"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Stear</ets>ic + <ets>ol</ets>eic + <ets>-ic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid of
the acetylene series, isologous with stearic acid, and obtained, as a
white crystalline substance, from oleic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stearone</ent>⟦br⟧
